President Cyril Ramaphosa withdraws from the Chairman's Conversation hosted by Power FM. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has withdrawn from the annual Chairman’s Conversation hosted by Power FM, the Presidency announced on Thursday. Ramaphosa was supposed to have a sit down with MSG Afrika chairman, Given Mkhari. The withdrawal by Ramaphosa comes after concerns from civil society. Mkhari previously hosted the likes of billionaire Johann Rupert and former president, Thabo Mbeki. READ THE FULL STATEMENT BY THE PRESIDENCY BELOW: